Objective:

Simulate basic banking operations in a console application, allowing users to create accounts,
 deposit/withdraw funds, view balances, and perform transfers.

Functional Requirements:

Account Management

Users can create a new bank account.

Required fields: Account Number (unique), Account Holder Name, Initial Balance.

Users can view account details.

Users can delete an account.

Transactions

Deposit: Add money to an account.

Withdraw: Remove money from an account (with balance check; cannot withdraw more than current balance).

Transfer: Move money from one account to another.

Transaction History: Optional: Keep a log of deposits, withdrawals, and transfers per account.

Account Lookup

Search for an account by account number.

List all accounts with basic details (name, account number, balance).

Input Validation

Validate user inputs (e.g., numbers for deposits/withdrawals, unique account numbers).

Handle invalid inputs gracefully without crashing.

Exit / Menu

Display a menu with options: Create Account, Deposit, Withdraw, Transfer, View Account, List Accounts, Exit.

Loop until the user chooses to exit.

Non-Functional Requirements:

Console-based user interface (text menu).

Use Object-Oriented Programming concepts:

BankAccount class for account representation.

Bank class or object to manage multiple accounts.

Use collections (List or Map) to store accounts.

Optional: Store transaction history using List inside each account.

Optional: Use when statements and functions for clean menu navigation.